For example, getting married requires you to have emotional understanding about what you are getting into, whereas drinking alcohol requires your body to have developed to the point where you can tolerate certain levels of alcohol and it wont impact further development. Therefore, I think that there should be a minimum age for irreversible, elective surgery. However, I am unsure about what age that should be, whether 16 or 18. I am no child developmental expert and so I would generally leave it to people better informed than I to make that decision.
